  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    AutonomousConfig
    A method annotation used to denote a method that specifies the autonomous config options for a subsystem.
    ConfigLabel

    An annotation that prevents a subsystem field in the robot class from being detected by the internal code, disabling it.
    ProgramOptions
    A class annotation used to easily put into place program configuration options.
    StandAlone
    A class annotation used to denote that an opmode is a stand-alone program.

    A method annotation used to denote a method that specifies the teleop config options for a subsystem.
